  schema:name "Claytonia perfoliata" ;
  schema:description "Annual succulent herb native to western North America, from Montiaceae family. Distinctive fused, orbicular cauline leaves (perfoliate) surround the inflorescence. Produces rapid leaf rosette and small white flowers; self-seeds readily. Grows in cool, moist conditions; partially shade-tolerant." ;
